Usage: verifyCutDensity [-help] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}] [-detailed]
                        [-globalDensity] [-ignoreCellBlock]
                        [-oversize <integer>] [-report <string>]
                        [-layer <string>]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}     # Specifies the coordinates of the area to verify
                        # (box, optional)
-detailed               # Generates a detailed cut density report
                        # (bool, optional)
-globalDensity          # Checks the density across the entire design for the
                        # specified cut layers and writes the results to the
                        # report file (bool, optional)
-ignoreCellBlock        # Ignore reporting the windows which are fully coverd
                        # by Block/Pad (bool, optional)
-layer <string>         # Specifies the cut layers to verify (string, optional)
-oversize <integer>     # Specifies an offset value for the area to verify
                        # (int, optional)
-report <string>        # Specifies the report file for the cut density
                        # violation information (string, optional)